President Barack Obama strongly condemns the terrorist attacks on a mosque in southeast Iran, expressing that the murder of innocent civilians in their place of worship is unacceptable. He calls for those responsible to be held accountable. The United States stands in solidarity with the families and loved ones of the victims, as well as the Iranian people. The President emphasizes the need for global condemnation and opposition to all forms of terrorism, while supporting the universal right of individuals to live free from fear and violence.